33. Default function parameters are bound statically. What happens here?
struct B {
    virtual void f(int x = 1) { std::cout << "B" << x; }
};
struct D : B {
    void f(int x = 2) override { std::cout << "D" << x; }
};
int main() {
    B* b = new D();
    b->f();
    delete b;
}
A) B1
B) D2
C) D1
D) B2

35. Constant pointers vs pointers to constants. Which of the lines will fail compile?
int x = 5;
const int* ptr1 = &x;
int* const ptr2 = &x;
// Line 1: *ptr1 = 10;
// Line 2: ptr2 = &x;
A) Line 1 only
B) Line 2 only
C) Both Line 1 and Line 2
D) Neither, both lines are completely valid

37. Lambda captures can hold references. What value is printed?
int x = 10;
auto lambda = [x]() mutable { x += 5; return x; };
lambda();
std::cout << x;
A) 10
B) 15
C) Compile Error: mutable is invalid on lambda without params
D) 0

